Part 1: Let’s suppose a car with a mass of 760 kg and that in 2 seconds is capable of going from 300 km/h to 265 km/h (standard atmospheric conditions: p = 3 1,225 kg/m perfect tire tread and no additional mechanical losses) in 2 seconds. What is its coefficient of resistance SC(x)?

Part 2: In order to establish a visual reference so that the driver knows when to start his manoeuvre, how many meters does the car travel in Coast Down?

Answer format: {Part 1}; {Part 2}
